The paper deals with data structures and algorithms for approximate range mode and range selection queries, which are fundamental problems in computational geometry and data analysis. The techniques used involve encoding data structures, dynamic data structures, and approximation algorithms, which are all core topics in computer science. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Other likely sub-categories include cs.CC (Computational Complexity), cs.IT (Information Theory), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics).
